commitResults.messageTitle: Add: Skeleton - greet, echo and exit functions
Add: Ability to store user input before displaying
commitResults.messageBody:
Text input from user is stored in a list (for now) and can be displayed
upon request using the command "list".

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: documentation for Duke main class
Add: Ability to mark tasks as done or undone
Add: Different task types - Todo, Event, Deadline
commitResults.messageBody:
User input (apart from the command "bye") must contain at least 4
characters and must follow the required format precisely.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: Change indentation for Duke's messages
commitResults.messageBody:
Increases indentation for Duke's output text from 4 to 5 spaces to
match project specification.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add: Tests for 6 basic commands using text UI
Fix: IOOBE - Change string method used
commitResults.messageBody:
Changes substring(...) to startsWith(...); fixes
IndexOutOfBoundsException but input is no longer case insensitive.
Added skeleton for handling exceptions.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add: Error handling - only 7 commands allowed
commitResults.messageBody:
Requires input to be of the form "bye", "list", "done [taskIndex]",
"undo [taskIndex]", "todo [description]", "deadline [description /by
[time]", or "event [description] /at [time]".

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: Access modifiers and method order.
commitResults.messageBody: Minor changes to clean up the code.

Users can remove tasks from the list using "delete [taskIndex]".
Tests have not been updated.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: Access modifiers and final variable names.
Fix: Minor format issues (comments, line breaks)
Refactor: Hide app logic in class DukeLogic

commitResults.messageBody:
Duke automatically saves to [root]/data/duke.txt whenever the task
list is modified. Output is formatted using toString().
No file reading functionality yet.

Duke recovers the task list from the previous session if a valid data file
is present. Data file must be properly formatted.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add: Date parsing for Events and Deadlines
commitResults.messageBody:
Duke now understands a limited range of date/time formats for Event timings
and Deadline due dates. Given an invalid date format, it substitutes the
current date/time.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: Merge issues - Date format for saving
commitResults.messageBody: Duke now loads hard disk data and runs correctly.

Previous order involved simpler patterns being parsed before more complex
ones, causing date info from duke.txt to be processed incorrectly.

commitResults.messageTitle: REFACTOR: Separate UI, storage, parser, Commands
commitResults.messageBody:
Reorganised code to extract out closely related sections as classes. Minimal
changes to working code i.e. not optimised yet.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor: Packages for duke, command, task
commitResults.messageBody:
Move Tasks and Commands into separate packages. Move Parser, Storage,
TextUi, and DukeException into duke package. Change access modifiers
accordingly.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: Move Duke main class to package duke
commitResults.messageBody: To make 'gradle run' work.
Add Checkstyle, Shadow (jar), and JUnit. Following Gradle tutorial.
To comply with the suggested checkstyle.
Part #1 of unit test requirement for A-JUnit.
Improve OOP practice and enable independent testing.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: Make Task getType() method public
commitResults.messageBody: For ease of testing.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add: Unit tests for Command and DeadlineCommand
commitResults.messageBody:
Test all key methods in classes. Use StorageStub to (partially) isolate
SUT.

Change build version. Allow Duke to automatically create a data log
file if it does not exist. Minor edit to UI welcome message.
Minimal Javadoc comments in certain places.

Enables basic searching of task list using any keyword contained
in the full task description.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: Spacing for existing javadoc comments
commitResults.messageBody:
Make minor tweaks to code style to satisfy A-CodingStandard
requirements. Code already passes Gradle checkstyle.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: JavaDoc comment style and access modifiers
commitResults.messageBody:
Added period '.' to certain one-line comments to comply with
checkstyle. Changed package-private access modifiers to public or
protected to better reflect access settings.

Set up Duke as a JavaFX application and create Launcher class
according to JavaFX Tutorial Part 1.

Set elements in position for Duke GUI, according to JavaFX Tutorial
Part 2.

Allow users to interact with Duke logic using GUI, following steps
from JavaFX Tutorial Part 3. User and Duke dialog boxes are displayed
in typical chat format on opposite sides of the screen. Details of
Duke's responses still need to be ironed out.

Not supported: Save functionality.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add: Basic FXML and separate Main class
commitResults.messageBody:
Following JavaFX Tutorial Part 4, use FXML to specify most of the
existing GUI features. Create a Main class and move GUI-related
code from Duke to MainWindow class.

This reverts commit b3f3be55aae9cf759fb6e80920dfe5b32b735010.
Accidentally merged branch-Level-10 to master and pushed to origin.
More GUI improvements to be made before merging.

Minor changes (e.g. add period after parameters) to comply with the
CS2103T coding standard.

Reorder @return and @throws statements in CommandTest and replace
wildcard import in CommandTest to pass Gradle checkstyle test.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor: Parser class to increase readability
commitResults.messageBody:
Make use of 'switch' statements, separate different types of validation,
move command-specific checks (i.e. "/at" and "/by") into respective
Command classes. Changes made in response to PR comments.

Also: Update version in build.gradle to v0.1.5.

* Add: Util and UI packages to improve organisation

Too many classes in main package duke. Parser, Storage, and TextUI
classes were moved into duke.util, and JavaFX classes into duke.ui.

Also fixes JavaDoc format for block tags in the classes that were
modified.

* Fix: Wrong path to MainWindow class

Path was not updated after previous refactor.

* Refactor: Date parsing and status icon checking

Refactor Task class for better OOP.
1. Move Date parsing functionality from Task into a separate DateParser.
2. Allow Task status icons to be changed without affecting other classes
such as HardDiskStorage.

* Fix: Wrong class paths in Test classes

Test classes were not updated after refactoring.
Update import statements for Storage and TextUi classes, and move
ParserTest into duke.util package.

* Fix: Application main class in build.gradle

Main class name of application was not updated after GUI was made.
Jar archives created using Gradle ShadowJar can now be run properly.

* Refactor: Command class constructors

Added more overloaded constructors in Command class, to eliminate calls
to super("") (empty string) from child classes.

* Add: Assertions and miscellaneous refactoring

Add assertions in key methods of various classes to check that the
internal logic is correct.

Miscellaneous improvements to code quality, including changing multiple
"if" blocks to switch statements.

* Refactor: toString() method to improve readability

Made use of Java Streams instead of a "for" loop to shorten the code.

* Fix: Minor style issues (variable names)

Replaced abbreviations with more descriptive names.

Allows users to mark Tasks with one out of four possible Priority
levels: High, Medium, Low, or None. Tasks with priority higher than
None are displayed with their priority level before task description.

Alternative keywords for priority levels Medium (e.g. mid, quite) and
None (no) are provided. Priority levels are NOT saved after exiting
Duke.
Add description of Priority enumeration, and other minor updates.
In preparation for next round of changes (after Priority).

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: Problems with Save functionality in GUI
commitResults.messageBody:
Duke has been unable to create the data file /data/duke.txt since
migrating from CLI to GUI. Issue was a missing relative file path.
Resolved by using System property "user.dir" when creating file path
in HardDiskStorage.

Also added load-tasks-from-disk functionality to the Duke constructor
used by JavaFX.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: Show found tasks with original index
commitResults.messageBody:
A FindCommand made a new list for found tasks, so index numbers shown
did not correspond to the numbers required for operations. Issue was
highlighted in peer review. Found Tasks are now displayed with their
original index numbers.

Command types (first word) can now be parsed regardless of what case
they are in.

Date parsing previously involved Date and SimpleDateFormat, which have
now been replaced by the newer Java classes LocalDateTime and
DateTimeFormatter.

To avoid having to change Task classes whenever DateParser is modified,
toString methods of time-related Tasks use a default date/time format
given by DateParser.
Remove unnecessary or completed TODO comments.

Remove maximum height for the dialog container so that Duke responses
(e.g. lists of tasks) can be viewed in their entirety.

Rebrands Duke as Snowball. Add welcome message when application is
launched. Create SpeechMaker class to handle Snowball speech.

Change user display picture. Add background and fix padding for dialog
box text.
So that more lines can be seen at a time.

Move more of Snowball's responses to the SpeechMaker class for better
OOP. Remove remaining references to Duke personality, along with unused
code. (The only use of Duke should be "the Duke application".)

commitResults.messageTitle: Add: Product name to title bar
commitResults.messageBody: Show product title in window title bar for clarity.

Implement storage and parsing of task Priority levels. Also, rename
TaskList indexed-string method as toIndexedString() for consistency with
toString() methods.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor: Task constructor to include Priority
commitResults.messageBody:
Improve the loading of existing tasks from storage by using overloaded
constructors to create new Tasks with differing Priority levels.

Minor Javadocs formatting changes.

Settle missing periods in Javadocs, indentation, etc. to pass Gradle
checkstyle.

Describe what Snowball is and how to use it. Add explanations for all
commands and command parameter restrictions. Include some examples, but
more examples can be shown especially for Add commands.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix: Minor format issues (date parsing & display)
commitResults.messageBody:
Add a shorter format for inputting dates conveniently. Make task lists
appear more presentable in Snowball's responses.

User Guide was mistakenly added to source README.md in a previous
